data.enText: afterwards; later; after sth else has happened

data.chText: 采访记录原稿后来丢失了。
data.enText: The original interview notes were subsequently lost.

data.chText: 随后，新的准则发给了所有雇员。
data.enText: Subsequently, new guidelines were issued to all employees.

tr: happening at a time subsequent to a reference time
example: he's going to the store but he'll be back here later

value.def: You use subsequent to describe something that happened or existed after the time or event that has just been referred to.

example.ex: ...the increase of population in subsequent years...
Those concerns were overshadowed by subsequent events.
example.tran: 随后发生的事使之前所关注的那些问题显得无足轻重。

example.ex: She subsequently became the Faculty's President...

example.tran: 后来这个计划被终止了。

value.def: If something happened subsequent to something else, it happened after that thing.

example.ex: They won only one more game subsequent to their Cup semi-final win last year.
example.tran: 继去年在杯赛半决赛中获胜后，他们仅又赢过一场比赛。
